<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="414" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11G93/757.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Hartman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 44.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 26, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your
                            unnumbered despatch of July 10, transmitting the answer of the Minister
                            for Foreign Affairs to your note of May 16 in regard to the Guayaquil
                            and Quito Railway Company, and requesting instructions as to your
                            procedure.</p>
                        <p>In reply you are informed that the Department does not consider it
                            necessary at the present time to make any reply to the note from the
                            Foreign Office.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>